The paper discusses the performance analysis of compressive sensing (CS) estimators using statistical mechanics and replica method. This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the analysis of multiple input multiple output (MIMO) systems, which falls under the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of Bayesian framework connects the CS estimators and replica method, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the one-step replica symmetry breaking (1RSB) ansatz, which is a technique used in optimization problems and falls under the Optimization and Control (cs.SI) sub-category.
